post_text: On behalf of the TRiO College and Career Readiness and Teen Outreach program, we would like to thank all high school participants that took time out of their spring break to attend the TRiO Youth Spring Camp in the beggining of March! Students also received the Making Proud Choices curriculum on health education and preventative life skills. Enjoy some fun learning moments from the camp!

post_text:
Hello Everyone,

We have a Medicare Educational Presentation coming up on Saturday, October 12th at 10am.

There is no cost to attend and it’s not a sales meeting. So if you or family members need help with understanding Medicare please join us.

The person presenting speaks Spanish as well.

Who Qualifies for Medicare?

Medicare is for individuals turning 65 years old, or individuals on disability for at least 24 months (any age).
Individuals must be citizens and residents for at least 5 consecutive years to qualify.
Individuals who also qualify for AHCCCS may have extra benefits available.

Please spread the word to community, friends and family. Thank you

Larry Fitzgerald
September 17, 2019 at 7:18 PM ·

Grateful for the opportunity to donate tablets to 32 schools here in the Valley...this area is my home, and it’s an honor to be able to help empower the next generation to build on the things we all love about this community.

Sending a huge thank you to Garth Brooks for being a part of this project. Your support and friendship mean the world to me.

Also want to shout out Microsoft for their work in helping us bring this technology to so many students!

Let’s all continue to work together to give our youth every chance they have to do amazing things 🙏🏾🙌🏾

Getting paid $450 to attend summer camp? The Maricopa County Sheriff's Office paid 30 teens from south and central Phoenix to attend a rigorous criminal justice careers camp. The three-week program exposed them to law enforcement careers as they got to meet public servants from DPS, Phoenix Police and MCSO. I covered the graduation ceremony yesterday. Lots of inspirational moments from kids and families. Bridges built. The nonprofit Friendly House helped make it possible.

Another TRiO Talent Search Senior Highlight:
Ramona Villegas is an outstanding student who has been our TRiO Program, since she was in middle school. She is graduating from AAEC-South Mountain High school with a 4.3 GPA! Not only is she acquiring a high school diploma with honors, but also an Associates Degree from South Mountain Community College. She will be finishing off her pre-requisites to study Nursing! What an accomplishment for her and her family! Friendly House and the TRiO Staff wish her much success and will continue to support her through her higher education path!
